Majid Mirbagheri received the Ph.D. and M.Sc. degrees in electrical and computer engineering from University of Maryland, College Park, USA in 2014 and 2008, respectively, and the B.Sc. degree in electrical engineering from Sharif University of Technology, Tehran, Iran in 2006. He is currently a post-doctoral research associate at the Institute for Learning and Brain Sciences and Department of Electrical Engineering at University of Washington, Seattle, WA, USA. His research interests include statistical machine learning, biological signal processing, and speech and audio signal processing.

